description: Describes the specified fraudster registration job.

parameters.name: DomainId
parameters.description: The identifier of the domain that contains the fraudster registration job.

parameters.name: JobId
parameters.description: The identifier of the fraudster registration job you are describing.

nested_items.name: CreatedAt
nested_items.description: A timestamp of when the fraudster registration job was created.

nested_items.name: DataAccessRoleArn
nested_items.description: The IAM role Amazon Resource Name (ARN) that grants Voice ID permissions to access customer's buckets to read the input manifest file and write the job output file.

nested_items.name: DomainId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the domain that contains the fraudster registration job.

nested_items.name: EndedAt
nested_items.description: A timestamp of when the fraudster registration job ended.

nested_items.name: FailureDetails
nested_items.description: Contains details that are populated when an entire batch job fails. In cases of individual registration job failures, the batch job as a whole doesn't fail; it is completed with a JobStatus of COMPLETED_WITH_ERRORS. You can use the job output file to identify the individual registration requests that failed.

nested_items.name: Message
nested_items.description: A description of the error that caused the batch job failure.

nested_items.name: StatusCode
nested_items.description: An HTTP status code representing the nature of the error.

nested_items.name: InputDataConfig
nested_items.description: The input data config containing an S3 URI for the input manifest file that contains the list of fraudster registration job requests.

nested_items.name: S3Uri
nested_items.description: The S3 location for the input manifest file that contains the list of individual enrollment or registration job requests.

nested_items.name: JobId
nested_items.description: The service-generated identifier for the fraudster registration job.

nested_items.name: JobName
nested_items.description: The client-provided name for the fraudster registration job.

nested_items.name: JobProgress
nested_items.description: Shows the completed percentage of registration requests listed in the input file.

nested_items.name: PercentComplete
nested_items.description: Shows the completed percentage of enrollment or registration requests listed in the input file.

nested_items.name: JobStatus
nested_items.description: The current status of the fraudster registration job.

nested_items.name: OutputDataConfig
nested_items.description: The output data config containing the S3 location where you want Voice ID to write your job output file; you must also include a KMS key ID in order to encrypt the file.

nested_items.name: KmsKeyId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the KMS key you want Voice ID to use to encrypt the output file of a speaker enrollment job/fraudster registration job.

nested_items.name: S3Uri
nested_items.description: The S3 path of the folder where Voice ID writes the job output file. It has a *.out extension. For example, if the input file name is input-file.json and the output folder path is s3://output-bucket/output-folder, the full output file path is s3://output-bucket/output-folder/job-Id/input-file.json.out.

nested_items.name: RegistrationConfig
nested_items.description: The registration config containing details such as the action to take when a duplicate fraudster is detected, and the similarity threshold to use for detecting a duplicate fraudster.

nested_items.name: DuplicateRegistrationAction
nested_items.description: The action to take when a fraudster is identified as a duplicate. The default action is SKIP, which skips registering the duplicate fraudster. Setting the value to REGISTER_AS_NEW always registers a new fraudster into the specified domain.

nested_items.name: FraudsterSimilarityThreshold
nested_items.description: The minimum similarity score between the new and old fraudsters in order to consider the new fraudster a duplicate.

nested_items.name: WatchlistIds
nested_items.description: The identifiers of watchlists that a fraudster is registered to. If a watchlist isn't provided, the fraudsters are registered to the default watchlist.
(string) ---
